eader(new InputStreamReader(is))));\\n            } finally {\\n                is.close();\\n            }\\n        }\\n        for (String s : names) {\\n            try{\\n                providers.add((PersistenceProvider)loader.loadClass(s).newInstance());\\n            } catch (ClassNotFoundException exc){\\n            } catch (InstantiationException exc){\\n            } catch (IllegalAccessException exc){\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final Pattern nonCommentPattern = Pattern.compile(\\\"^([^#]+)\\\");\\n\\n    private static Set<String> providerNamesFromReader(BufferedReader reader) throws IOException {\\n        Set<String> names = new HashSet<String>();\\n        String line;\\n        while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {\\n            line = line.trim();\\n            Matcher m = nonCommentPattern.matcher(line);\\n            if (m.find()) {\\n                names.add(m.group().trim());\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return names;\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777322924758}}\n1304:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Determining source path**\\n\\nI need to check if I require an absolute path outside the current working directory. The path I have is \\\"/home/vjovanov/c/forge2/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context...\\\" so I’ll definitely need to use that absolute path. It seems straightforward, but I want to make sure I'm clear on how this works to avoid issues later. I'll focus on confirming that everything is correct!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_06575ac38c69ad860169efcbaa61c881939137fd5db7b0f43e\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp78usrdRvf1U-8LJlANR6C-1azWqXFT0HNbei33t00EawLIg7rhWv9W6CG4EpudpOTujw3AqngSyDoMWkAVPV7P9V85nBrnWfuZcpBooTKbXfaf1AFmbU1KIr4og_4mmyWSbd99IgN4D58IY8ucttbJVl-xi55L84v10UGacD9FNCkgcKs7iG2nnX049SWrVQiBA